{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0117TQdfd2KgoFNXVkYuDnbH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 15-5: Lint Rule for Bare Exception Swallowing\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer,\n     8→I want code review to flag `except Exception: pass` (Python) and empty catch blocks,\n     9→So that error swallowing doesn't cause silent production incidents.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given code-review subagent reviews Python code, when it finds `except Exception: pass`, then it flags it as HIGH severity <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given `post-write-check.sh` hook runs after writing a Python file, when the file contains `except Exception: pass`, then it prints a warning <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→\n    16→## Technical Notes\n    17→\n    18→**Decision 7 (Error Handling).** This story extends error-handling enforcement beyond TypeScript to Python code reviewed or generated by codeharness.\n    19→\n    20→### Semgrep Rule for Python (AC1)\n    21→\n    22→Create a Semgrep rule in `patches/observability/` (or a new `patches/error-handling/` directory) that catches bare exception swallowing in Python:\n    23→\n    24→```yaml\n    25→# patches/error-handling/no-bare-except.yaml\n    26→rules:\n    27→  - id: no-bare-except-pass\n    28→    pattern: |\n    29→      try:\n    30→        ...\n    31→      except Exception:\n    32→        pass\n    33→    message: \"Bare `except Exception: pass` swallows errors silently. Handle the error, log it, or add a # IGNORE: comment explaining why.\"\n    34→    severity: ERROR\n    35→    languages: [python]\n    36→    metadata:\n    37→      category: error-handling\n    38→      confidence: HIGH\n    39→\n    40→  - id: no-bare-except-ellipsis\n    41→    pattern: |\n    42→      try:\n    43→        ...\n    44→      except Exception:\n    45→        ...\n    46→    message: \"Bare `except Exception: ...` swallows errors silently.\"\n    47→    severity: ERROR\n    48→    languages: [python]\n    49→```\n    50→\n    51→The code-review subagent (in `src/modules/review/orchestrator.ts`) should include this Semgrep rule when reviewing Python files. The review module already runs Semgrep as part of its analysis -- add this rule to the rule set.\n    52→\n    53→### Post-write Hook (AC2)\n    54→\n    55→Create or update `hooks/post-write-check.sh` (Claude Code plugin hook) to check Python files after they're written:\n    56→\n    57→```bash\n    58→# Check for bare except swallowing in Python files\n    59→if [[ \"$FILE\" == *.py ]]; then\n    60→  if grep -n \"except Exception.*pass\" \"$FILE\"; then\n    61→    echo \"[WARN] Bare 'except Exception: pass' detected in $FILE\"\n    62→    echo \"       Handle the error or add a # IGNORE: comment\"\n    63→  fi\n    64→fi\n    65→```\n    66→\n    67→This hook fires in Claude Code after a file write, giving immediate feedback during development.\n    68→\n    69→### Integration with Code Review\n    70→\n    71→In `src/modules/review/orchestrator.ts`, ensure the Semgrep rule scan includes:\n    72→1. The new `patches/error-handling/` rules\n    73→2. Python files in the review scope\n    74→3. Severity mapping: Semgrep `ERROR` -> review `HIGH` severity finding\n    75→\n    76→## Files to Change\n    77→\n    78→- `patches/error-handling/no-bare-except.yaml` — Create. Semgrep rules for Python bare exception swallowing\n    79→- `hooks/post-write-check.sh` — Update or create. Add Python bare-except detection after file writes\n    80→- `src/modules/review/orchestrator.ts` — Include error-handling Semgrep rules in code review scan\n    81→- `src/lib/scanner.ts` — Ensure Semgrep scanner can load rules from `patches/error-handling/` directory\n    82→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3fcb2b1c-e710-401b-91ab-b64a3e9a3996","uuid":"43800bf3-992c-4560-a47e-b9fa2269d6be","timestamp":"2026-03-25T06:52:32.775Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/15-5-lint-rule-bare-exception-swallowing.md","content":"# Story 15-5: Lint Rule for Bare Exception Swallowing\n\n## Status: backlog\n\n## Story\n\nAs a developer,\nI want code review to flag `except Exception: pass` (Python) and empty catch blocks,\nSo that error swallowing doesn't cause silent production incidents.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC1: Given code-review subagent reviews Python code, when it finds `except Exception: pass`, then it flags it as HIGH severity <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [ ] AC2: Given `post-write-check.sh` hook runs after writing a Python file, when the file contains `except Exception: pass`, then it prints a warning <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n\n## Technical Notes\n\n**Decision 7 (Error Handling).** This story extends error-handling enforcement beyond TypeScript to Python code reviewed or generated by codeharness.\n\n### Semgrep Rule for Python (AC1)\n\nCreate a Semgrep rule in `patches/observability/` (or a new `patches/error-handling/` directory) that catches bare exception swallowing in Python:\n\n```yaml\n# patches/error-handling/no-bare-except.yaml\nrules:\n  - id: no-bare-except-pass\n    pattern: |\n      try:\n        ...\n      except Exception:\n        pass\n    message: \"Bare `except Exception: pass` swallows errors silently. Handle the error, log it, or add a # IGNORE: comment explaining why.\"\n    severity: ERROR\n    languages: [python]\n    metadata:\n      category: error-handling\n      confidence: HIGH\n\n  - id: no-bare-except-ellipsis\n    pattern: |\n      try:\n        ...\n      except Exception:\n        ...\n    message: \"Bare `except Exception: ...` swallows errors silently.\"\n    severity: ERROR\n    languages: [python]\n```\n\nThe code-review subagent (in `src/modules/review/orchestrator.ts`) should include this Semgrep rule when reviewing Python files. The review module already runs Semgrep as part of its analysis -- add this rule to the rule set.\n\n### Post-write Hook (AC2)\n\nCreate or update `hooks/post-write-check.sh` (Claude Code plugin hook) to check Python files after they're written:\n\n```bash\n# Check for bare except swallowing in Python files\nif [[ \"$FILE\" == *.py ]]; then\n  if grep -n \"except Exception.*pass\" \"$FILE\"; then\n    echo \"[WARN] Bare 'except Exception: pass' detected in $FILE\"\n    echo \"       Handle the error or add a # IGNORE: comment\"\n  fi\nfi\n```\n\nThis hook fires in Claude Code after a file write, giving immediate feedback during development.\n\n### Integration with Code Review\n\nIn `src/modules/review/orchestrator.ts`, ensure the Semgrep rule scan includes:\n1. The new `patches/error-handling/` rules\n2. Python files in the review scope\n3. Severity mapping: Semgrep `ERROR` -> review `HIGH` severity finding\n\n## Files to Change\n\n- `patches/error-handling/no-bare-except.yaml` — Create. Semgrep rules for Python bare exception swallowing\n- `hooks/post-write-check.sh` — Update or create. Add Python bare-except detection after file writes\n- `src/modules/review/orchestrator.ts` — Include error-handling Semgrep rules in code review scan\n- `src/lib/scanner.ts` — Ensure Semgrep scanner can load rules from `patches/error-handling/` directory\n","numLines":82,"startLine":1,"totalLines":82}}}
