{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QNGLYMg645ZYLSXXr6ENg2","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Review Module\n     2→\n     3→Code review execution. Invokes BMAD code-review workflow via child_process and returns structured results.\n     4→\n     5→## Files\n     6→\n     7→- `index.ts` — Public API: `reviewStory(key, opts?)` — delegates to orchestrator, re-exports `ReviewResult` type. Only public interface for the module.\n     8→- `orchestrator.ts` — Workflow invocation: `invokeBmadCodeReview(key, opts?)` — spawns `claude --print` with BMAD code-review prompt, parses review output for approval/rejection signals, extracts comment lines. Handles timeout (killed/SIGTERM) and non-zero exit errors. Internal to module.\n     9→- `types.ts` — Module-specific types: `ReviewResult` (key, approved, comments, duration, output — all readonly)\n    10→- `__tests__/observability-patch.test.ts` — Validates that `patches/review/enforcement.md` and `patches/dev/enforcement.md` contain required observability sections and Semgrep instructions. Also validates Semgrep JSON output format contract.\n    11→\n    12→## Patterns\n    13→\n    14→- All public functions return `Result<T>` (never throw)\n    15→- Uses `execFileSync` for main workflow\n    16→- ES module imports with `.js` extensions\n    17→- Default timeout: 25 minutes (1,500,000ms)\n    18→- Output truncated to last 200 lines\n    19→- Approval detection uses heuristic keyword matching on review output\n    20→- Defaults to `approved: true` when no rejection signals detected\n    21→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MaiZ71xHuWaWxP6B1wGjKe","session_id":"3fcb2b1c-e710-401b-91ab-b64a3e9a3996","uuid":"6219249c-c016-4d3f-aca5-b56f9f3c9032","timestamp":"2026-03-25T06:53:16.497Z"}
