{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Ekt5Z7RerS7S8sgYbABeoP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→## WHY\n     2→\n     3→Review agents approved stories without verifying proof documents existed or\n     4→checking that evidence was black-box (not source-grep). Stories passed review\n     5→with fabricated output and missing coverage data. This patch enforces proof\n     6→existence, black-box evidence quality, and coverage delta reporting as hard\n     7→gates before a story can leave review.\n     8→(FR33, FR34, NFR20)\n     9→\n    10→## Codeharness Review Gates\n    11→\n    12→### Verification Proof\n    13→\n    14→- Proof document exists at `verification/<story-key>-proof.md`\n    15→- Proof passes `codeharness verify --story <id>` (parser checks for FAIL/ESCALATE verdicts)\n    16→- Every AC has functional evidence — reading docs alone is not evidence\n    17→- No fabricated output — all evidence must be from actual command execution\n    18→\n    19→### Proof Quality Checks\n    20→\n    21→The proof must pass black-box enforcement:\n    22→- Commands run via `docker exec` (not direct host access)\n    23→- Less than 50% of evidence commands are `grep` against `src/`\n    24→- Each AC section has at least one `docker exec`, `docker ps/logs`, or observability query\n    25→- `[FAIL]` verdicts outside code blocks cause the proof to fail\n    26→- `[ESCALATE]` is acceptable only when all automated approaches are exhausted\n    27→\n    28→### Observability\n    29→\n    30→Run `semgrep scan --config patches/observability/ --json` against changed files and report gaps.\n    31→\n    32→- For each gap found, list it as a review issue: file path, line number, and description (e.g., \"src/lib/docker.ts:42 — catch block without logging\")\n    33→- Semgrep JSON output fields to extract: `check_id`, `path`, `start.line`, `extra.message`\n    34→- If zero observability gaps are found, this check passes silently — do not emit warnings\n    35→- If Semgrep is not installed, report \"static analysis skipped — install semgrep\" as a warning and do NOT fail the review\n    36→\n    37→### Code Quality\n    38→\n    39→- Coverage delta reported (before vs after)\n    40→- No coverage regression in changed files\n    41→- AGENTS.md is current for all changed modules\n    42→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MaiZ71xHuWaWxP6B1wGjKe","session_id":"3fcb2b1c-e710-401b-91ab-b64a3e9a3996","uuid":"9204562c-dda0-4d03-8485-e5c53360451d","timestamp":"2026-03-25T06:53:20.676Z"}
