{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q3RFHXWsqGXCU1UinL5VYz","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→## WHY\n     2→\n     3→Dev agents repeatedly shipped code without reading module conventions (AGENTS.md),\n     4→skipped observability checks, and produced features that could not be verified\n     5→from outside the source tree. This patch enforces architecture awareness,\n     6→observability validation, documentation hygiene, test coverage gates, and\n     7→black-box thinking — all operational failures observed in prior sprints.\n     8→(FR33, FR34, NFR20)\n     9→\n    10→## Codeharness Development Enforcement\n    11→\n    12→### Architecture Awareness\n    13→\n    14→Before writing code, read the relevant `AGENTS.md` file for the module being changed. Understand:\n    15→- Build commands and test runners\n    16→- Module boundaries and conventions\n    17→- What NOT to do (common pitfalls documented from prior incidents)\n    18→\n    19→### Observability\n    20→\n    21→Run `semgrep scan --config patches/observability/` before committing and fix any gaps.\n    22→\n    23→After running tests, verify telemetry is flowing:\n    24→- Query VictoriaLogs to confirm log events from test runs\n    25→- If observability is configured, traces should be visible for CLI operations\n    26→\n    27→### Documentation\n    28→\n    29→- Update `AGENTS.md` for all changed modules\n    30→- Keep exec-plan current with implementation state\n    31→\n    32→### Testing\n    33→\n    34→- All tests pass before moving to review\n    35→- Coverage gate: 100% of new/changed code\n    36→- Run `npm test` / `pytest` and verify no regressions\n    37→\n    38→### Black-Box Thinking\n    39→\n    40→Write code that can be verified from the outside. Ask yourself:\n    41→- Can a user exercise this feature from the CLI alone?\n    42→- Is the behavior documented in README.md?\n    43→- Would a verifier with NO source access be able to tell if this works?\n    44→\n    45→If the answer is \"no\", the feature has a testability gap — fix the CLI/docs, not the verification process.\n    46→\n    47→### Dockerfile Maintenance\n    48→\n    49→If this story adds a new runtime dependency, check whether the Dockerfile needs updating:\n    50→- New system package required at runtime (e.g., `libssl`, `ffmpeg`) — add to `apt-get install` line\n    51→- New binary expected on PATH — add install step to Dockerfile\n    52→- New Python package needed — add to `pip install` or `requirements.txt` COPY\n    53→- Verify the updated Dockerfile still passes `validateDockerfile()` with zero gaps\n    54→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01MaiZ71xHuWaWxP6B1wGjKe","session_id":"3fcb2b1c-e710-401b-91ab-b64a3e9a3996","uuid":"84d714ca-71b0-4c26-a748-a8c61842b9d2","timestamp":"2026-03-25T06:53:21.102Z"}
