t the additional error-handling config arg\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/review/__tests__/observability-patch.test.ts` -- Updated 1 existing test to match new semgrep command format\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/15-5-lint-rule-bare-exception-swallowing.md` -- Status changed to `review`\n\n### Test Results\nAll 3799 tests pass across 147 test files. Zero regressions.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **scanner.ts not changed**: The story lists `src/lib/scanner.ts` as a file to change, but that file is a codebase module/coverage scanner -- it has no Semgrep integration. The Semgrep rule loading lives entirely in `src/modules/observability/analyzer.ts`, which was updated instead.\n- **Semgrep test fixtures not runnable without semgrep**: The `patches/error-handling/__tests__/no-bare-except.py` fixtures use standard Semgrep `# ruleid:` / `# ok:` annotation format, but can only be validated by running `semgrep --test patches/error-handling/` which requires semgrep to be installed. The vitest tests validate file existence and content but not Semgrep pattern matching.\n- **`no-bare-except-ellipsis` rule may be overly broad**: The pattern `except Exception: ...` uses Semgrep's `...` metavariable, which matches any body content -- this means it will flag ALL `except Exception:` blocks, not just those with literal Python `...` (Ellipsis). This is actually the correct behavior per AC1 (flag all bare exception swallowing), but worth noting the rule name is slightly misleading if read literally.\n- **Hook grep pattern is approximate**: The `grep -n \"except Exception.*pass\"` in post-write-check.sh would match commented-out code or strings containing the pattern. A full Semgrep scan is more accurate; the hook is a fast heuristic for immediate feedback."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: ab65c70a9f4736d73 (use SendMessage with to: 'ab65c70a9f4736d73' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 68490\ntool_uses