emgrep --test patches/error-handling/` which requires semgrep to be installed. The vitest tests validate file existence and content but not Semgrep pattern matching.\n- **`no-bare-except-ellipsis` rule may be overly broad**: The pattern `except Exception: ...` uses Semgrep's `...` metavariable, which matches any body content -- this means it will flag ALL `except Exception:` blocks, not just those with literal Python `...` (Ellipsis). This is actually the correct behavior per AC1 (flag all bare exception swallowing), but worth noting the rule name is slightly misleading if read literally.\n- **Hook grep pattern is approximate**: The `grep -n \"except Exception.*pass\"` in post-write-check.sh would match commented-out code or strings containing the pattern. A full Semgrep scan is more accurate; the hook is a fast heuristic for immediate feedback."}],"totalDurationMs":267742,"totalTokens":68490,"totalToolUseCount":52,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":249,"cache_read_input_tokens":67162,"output_tokens":1078,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":249},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
