{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015YndURAg3ydonu7fr45iNH","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Observability Module\n     2→\n     3→Static analysis of observability coverage (logging gaps, error handler coverage) and coverage state tracking over time.\n     4→\n     5→## Files\n     6→\n     7→- `index.ts` — Public API barrel: re-exports `analyze` from analyzer, `saveCoverageResult`, `readCoverageState`, `getCoverageTrend`, `checkCoverageTarget` from coverage, and all public types.\n     8→- `analyzer.ts` — Static analysis runner: `analyze(projectDir, config?)` — runs Semgrep (or skips gracefully if not installed), parses results into tool-agnostic `AnalyzerResult`. Also exports `checkSemgrepInstalled`, `runSemgrep`, `parseSemgrepOutput`, `computeSummary`.\n     9→- `coverage.ts` — Coverage state persistence: `saveCoverageResult(projectDir, result)` — writes coverage to sprint-state.json atomically, appends to history. `readCoverageState(projectDir)` — reads typed coverage state. `getCoverageTrend(projectDir)` — compares latest vs previous history entry. `checkCoverageTarget(projectDir, target?)` — checks coverage against target (default 80%).\n    10→- `coverage-gate.ts` — Commit gate check: `checkObservabilityCoverageGate(projectDir, overrides?)` — reads cached static and runtime coverage from sprint-state.json, compares against targets. Does NOT re-run Semgrep. Static is always required; runtime only checked when data exists. Returns `ObservabilityCoverageGateResult`.\n    11→- `runtime-coverage.ts` — Runtime coverage persistence: `computeRuntimeCoverage(gaps, totalACs)` — computes runtime coverage from verification observability gaps. `saveRuntimeCoverage(projectDir, result)` — writes runtime coverage to sprint-state.json atomically.\n    12→- `runtime-validator.ts` — Standalone runtime validator (Story 2.3): `validateRuntime(projectDir, config?)` — runs tests with OTLP enabled, queries VictoriaLogs for telemetry events, computes per-module coverage. `checkBackendHealth(queryEndpoint)` — checks if observability backend is reachable. `queryTelemetryEvents(queryEndpoint, start, end)` — queries VictoriaLogs for events in time window. `mapEventsToModules(events, projectDir, modules?)` — groups events by module name.\n    13→- `types.ts` — All interfaces: `AnalyzerResult`, `AnalyzerConfig`, `AnalyzerSummary`, `ObservabilityGap`, `GapSeverity`, `SemgrepRawOutput`, `SemgrepResult`, `ObservabilityCoverageState`, `StaticCoverageState`, `CoverageTargets`, `CoverageHistoryEntry`, `CoverageTrend`, `CoverageTargetResult`, `ObservabilityCoverageGateResult`, `RuntimeCoverageEntry`, `RuntimeCoverageResult`, `RuntimeCoverageState`, `RuntimeValidationConfig`, `ModuleTelemetryEntry`, `RuntimeValidationResult`, `TelemetryEvent`.\n    14→\n    15→## Patterns\n    16→\n    17→- All public functions return `Result<T>` (never throw)\n    18→- Atomic writes via temp file + `renameSync` (same pattern as sprint/state.ts)\n    19→- ES module imports with `.js` extensions\n    20→- Coverage state stored in `sprint-state.json` under `observability` key\n    21→- Static and runtime coverage tracked separately (architecture Decision 2)\n    22→- Gate checks use cached state only — no Semgrep re-runs in hooks for performance\n    23→- Standalone runtime validation: health-check backend first, skip gracefully if unavailable\n    24→- Module discovery: scans top-level directories under src/ to determine project modules\n    25→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01RaXV75NMTprbvd4KMPDvjb","session_id":"3fcb2b1c-e710-401b-91ab-b64a3e9a3996","uuid":"9386a2f0-935a-4290-8090-b60d94012443","timestamp":"2026-03-25T07:01:54.731Z"}
