nly detected `pass` but not Python Ellipsis `...` pattern\n- MEDIUM: AGENTS.md stale for observability module after `additionalRulesDirs` config addition\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- Story \"Files to Change\" lists `src/lib/scanner.ts` but it was never modified — the change correctly went to `analyzer.ts` instead. Story spec inaccuracy, not a code issue.\n- Missing Showboat proof document for this story\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- None. 97.11% overall, all files above 80% floor.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- The `pattern-regex` approach for `no-bare-except-ellipsis` is less precise than AST-based Semgrep patterns — it won't handle edge cases like multiline exception clauses or unusual indentation. However, it's the only reliable way to match Python's literal `...` in Semgrep without false positives. Acceptable tradeoff.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed. Story moved to `verifying`."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: af7cad5d8e9d45fc4 (use SendMessage with to: 'af7cad5d8e9d45fc4' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 59727\ntool_uses: 58\nduration_ms: 338047</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3fcb2b1c-e710-401b-91ab-b64a3e9a3996","uuid":"e0fcccc7-1450-4a71-a238-40ea3bf7bc60","timestamp":"2026-03-25T07:03:43.347Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/15-5-lint-rule-bare-exception-swallowing.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing