{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019PMxhzxgmJpAMafuunzmpu","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/15-5-lint-rule-bare-exception-swallowing.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3fcb2b1c-e710-401b-91ab-b64a3e9a3996","uuid":"f602b84a-4281-4ac5-8319-4705019b0d18","timestamp":"2026-03-25T07:04:35.560Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/15-5-lint-rule-bare-exception-swallowing.md","oldString":"# Story 15-5: Lint Rule for Bare Exception Swallowing","newString":"<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->\n# Story 15-5: Lint Rule for Bare Exception Swallowing","originalFile":"# Story 15-5: Lint Rule for Bare Exception Swallowing\n\n## Status: verifying\n\n## Story\n\nAs a developer,\nI want code review to flag `except Exception: pass` (Python) and empty catch blocks,\nSo that error swallowing doesn't cause silent production incidents.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC1: Given code-review subagent reviews Python code, when it finds `except Exception: pass`, then it flags it as HIGH severity <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n- [ ] AC2: Given `post-write-check.sh` hook runs after writing a Python file, when the file contains `except Exception: pass`, then it prints a warning <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n\n## Technical Notes\n\n**Decision 7 (Error Handling).** This story extends error-handling enforcement beyond TypeScript to Python code reviewed or generated by codeharness.\n\n### Semgrep Rule for Python (AC1)\n\nCreate a Semgrep rule in `patches/observability/` (or a new `patches/error-handling/` directory) that catches bare exception swallowing in Python:\n\n```yaml\n# patches/error-handling/no-bare-except.yaml\nrules:\n  - id: no-bare-except-pass\n    pattern: |\n      try:\n        ...\n      except Exception:\n        pass\n    message: \"Bare `except Exception: pass` swallows errors silently. Handle the error, log it, or add a # IGNORE: comment explaining why.\"\n    severity: ERROR\n    languages: [python]\n    metadata:\n      category: error-handling\n      confidence: HIGH\n\n  - id: no-bare-except-ellipsis\n    pattern: |\n      try:\n        ...\n      except Exception:\n        ...\n    message: \"Bare `except Exception: ...` swallows errors silently.\"\n    severity: ERROR\n    languages: [python]\n```\n\nThe code-review subagent (in `src/modules/review/orchestrator.ts`) should include this Semgrep rule when reviewing Python files. The review module already runs Semgrep as part of its analysis -- add this rule to the rule set.\n\n### Post-write Hook (AC2)\n\nCreate or update `hooks/post-write-check.sh` (Claude Code plugin hook) to check Python files after they're written:\n\n```bash\n# Check for bare except swallowing in Python files\nif [[ \"$FILE\" == *.py ]]; then\n  if grep -n \"except Exception.*pass\" \"$FILE\"; then\n    echo \"[WARN] Bare 'except Exception: pass' detected in $FILE\"\n    echo \"       Handle the error or add a # IGNORE: comment\"\n  fi\nfi\n```\n\nThis hook fires in Claude Code after a file write, giving immediate feedback during development.\n\n### Integration with Code Review\n\nIn `src/modules/review/orchestrator.ts`, ensure the Semgrep rule scan includes:\n1. The new `patches/error-handling/` rules\n2. Python files in the review scope\n3. Severity mapping: Semgrep `ERROR` -> review `HIGH` severity finding\n\n## Files to Change\n\n- `patches/error-handling/no-bare-except.yaml` — Create. Semgrep rules for Python bare exception swallowing\n- `hooks/post-write-check.sh` — Update or create. Add Python bare-except detection after file writes\n- `src/modules/review/orchestrator.ts` — Include error-handling Semgrep rules in code review scan\n- `src/lib/scanner.ts` — Ensure Semgrep scanner can load rules from `patches/error-handling/` directory\n\n## Senior Developer Review (AI)\n\n**Reviewer:** Code Review Agent, 2026-03-25\n**Outcome:** Changes Requested -> Fixed\n\n### Issues Found and Fixed\n\n| # | Severity | Issue | Fix |\n|---|----------|-------|-----|\n| H1 | HIGH | Hook grep pattern `except Exception.*pass` never matches — `pass` is always on the next line in Python. AC2 was broken. | Replaced with awk-based multiline detection that checks the line following `except Exception:` for `pass` or `...` |\n| H2 | HIGH | `no-bare-except-ellipsis` Semgrep rule used `...` (Semgrep wildcard) in except body, matching ALL `except Exception:` blocks regardless of content. False positive machine. | Replaced with `pattern-regex` targeting literal `...` on the line after `except Exception:` |\n| M1 | MEDIUM | Hook only detected `pass` pattern, not Python's `...` (Ellipsis) | Fixed as part of H1 — awk now detects both `pass` and `...` |\n| M2 | MEDIUM | AGENTS.md for observability module not updated with new `additionalRulesDirs` config | Updated AGENTS.md |\n\n### Issues Not Fixed (LOW)\n\n- L1: `src/lib/scanner.ts` listed in story \"Files to Change\" but not modified — story spec was incorrect, change correctly went to `analyzer.ts`\n- L2: Missing Showboat proof document\n\n### Coverage\n\n- Overall: 97.11% (target: 90%) — PASS\n- Per-file floor: all 156 files above 80% — PASS\n- Tests: 147 passed, 0 failed\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":1,"oldLines":3,"newStart":1,"newLines":4,"lines":["+<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->"," # Story 15-5: Lint Rule for Bare Exception Swallowing"," "," ## Status: verifying"]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
