ook warns on Python bare exception\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\n**Evidence:**\n\n1. Hook at `hooks/post-write-check.sh` includes awk-based multiline detection for `except Exception:` followed by `pass` or `...`\n2. Live test with sample Python file containing both patterns:\n\n```\ninput: echo '{\"file_path\": \"/tmp/test_bare_except.py\"}' | bash hooks/post-write-check.sh\noutput: {\"message\": \"New code written. Verify OTLP instrumentation is present.\\n-> Check that new endpoints emit traces and structured logs.\\n[WARN] Bare 'except Exception: pass/...' detected in /tmp/test_bare_except.py\\n       Handle the error or add a # IGNORE: comment\"}\n```\n\n3. 4 dedicated tests pass in `error-handling-enforcement.test.ts` confirming:\n   - Checks for `.py` file extension\n   - Uses awk for multiline detection\n   - Emits `[WARN]` message\n   - Suggests handling error or adding IGNORE comment\n\n## Summary\n\n| AC | Verdict | Method |\n|----|---------|--------|\n| AC1 | PASS | Source inspection + test execution |\n| AC2 | PASS | Live hook execution + test execution |\n\n**All ACs verified. Story ready to mark done.**\n\n<!-- verification-summary: passed=2, failed=0, escalated=0, pending=0 -->\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
