{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BnxSm7N6UVF7gCEW37fv6t","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Verification Proof: 15-5-lint-rule-bare-exception-swallowing\n     2→\n     3→**Story:** Lint Rule for Bare Exception Swallowing\n     4→**Verified:** 2026-03-25\n     5→**Method:** Unit-testable (all ACs cli-verifiable)\n     6→\n     7→## AC 1: Semgrep rule flags `except Exception: pass` as HIGH severity\n     8→\n     9→**Verdict:** PASS\n    10→\n    11→**Evidence:**\n    12→\n    13→1. Semgrep rule file exists at `patches/error-handling/no-bare-except.yaml`\n    14→2. Rule `no-bare-except-pass` targets Python with `severity: ERROR` and `confidence: HIGH`\n    15→3. Rule `no-bare-except-ellipsis` also targets Python with same severity\n    16→4. Analyzer integration at `src/modules/observability/analyzer.ts` includes `ADDITIONAL_RULES_DIRS = ['patches/error-handling/']`\n    17→5. Review enforcement at `patches/review/enforcement.md` includes `--config patches/error-handling/` in semgrep command\n    18→6. Dev enforcement at `patches/dev/enforcement.md` includes same config\n    19→7. 10 dedicated tests pass in `error-handling-rules.test.ts` confirming:\n    20→   - `parseSemgrepOutput` maps findings with error severity\n    21→   - `analyze()` includes error-handling rules by default\n    22→   - `runSemgrep()` passes additional rule dirs as separate `--config` args\n    23→\n    24→```\n    25→output: All 10 tests in error-handling-rules.test.ts PASS\n    26→output: Rule file contains no-bare-except-pass (severity: ERROR, confidence: HIGH)\n    27→output: Review enforcement includes --config patches/error-handling/\n    28→```\n    29→\n    30→## AC 2: `post-write-check.sh` hook warns on Python bare exception\n    31→\n    32→**Verdict:** PASS\n    33→\n    34→**Evidence:**\n    35→\n    36→1. Hook at `hooks/post-write-check.sh` includes awk-based multiline detection for `except Exception:` followed by `pass` or `...`\n    37→2. Live test with sample Python file containing both patterns:\n    38→\n    39→```\n    40→input: echo '{\"file_path\": \"/tmp/test_bare_except.py\"}' | bash hooks/post-write-check.sh\n    41→output: {\"message\": \"New code written. Verify OTLP instrumentation is present.\\n-> Check that new endpoints emit traces and structured logs.\\n[WARN] Bare 'except Exception: pass/...' detected in /tmp/test_bare_except.py\\n       Handle the error or add a # IGNORE: comment\"}\n    42→```\n    43→\n    44→3. 4 dedicated tests pass in `error-handling-enforcement.test.ts` confirming:\n    45→   - Checks for `.py` file extension\n    46→   - Uses awk for multiline detection\n    47→   - Emits `[WARN]` message\n    48→   - Suggests handling error or adding IGNORE comment\n    49→\n    50→## Summary\n    51→\n    52→| AC | Verdict | Method |\n    53→|----|---------|--------|\n    54→| AC1 | PASS | Source inspection + test execution |\n    55→| AC2 | PASS | Live hook execution + test execution |\n    56→\n    57→**All ACs verified. Story ready to mark done.**\n    58→\n    59→<!-- verification-summary: passed=2, failed=0, escalated=0, pending=0 -->\n    60→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3fcb2b1c-e710-401b-91ab-b64a3e9a3996","uuid":"398c8a8c-79ae-4898-8b12-fceb64b4f34c","timestamp":"2026-03-25T07:10:50.908Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/verification/15-5-lint-rule-bare-exception-swallowing-proof.md","content":"# Verification Proof: 15-5-lint-rule-bare-exception-swallowing\n\n**Story:** Lint Rule for Bare Exception Swallowing\n**Verified:** 2026-03-25\n**Method:** Unit-testable (all ACs cli-verifiable)\n\n## AC 1: Semgrep rule flags `except Exception: pass` as HIGH severity\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\n**Evidence:**\n\n1. Semgrep rule file exists at `patches/error-handling/no-bare-except.yaml`\n2. Rule `no-bare-except-pass` targets Python with `severity: ERROR` and `confidence: HIGH`\n3. Rule `no-bare-except-ellipsis` also targets Python with same severity\n4. Analyzer integration at `src/modules/observability/analyzer.ts` includes `ADDITIONAL_RULES_DIRS = ['patches/error-handling/']`\n5. Review enforcement at `patches/review/enforcement.md` includes `--config patches/error-handling/` in semgrep command\n6. Dev enforcement at `patches/dev/enforcement.md` includes same config\n7. 10 dedicated tests pass in `error-handling-rules.test.ts` confirming:\n   - `parseSemgrepOutput` maps findings with error severity\n   - `analyze()` includes error-handling rules by default\n   - `runSemgrep()` passes additional rule dirs as separate `--config` args\n\n```\noutput: All 10 tests in error-handling-rules.test.ts PASS\noutput: Rule file contains no-bare-except-pass (severity: ERROR, confidence: HIGH)\noutput: Review enforcement includes --config patches/error-handling/\n```\n\n## AC 2: `post-write-check.sh` hook warns on Python bare exception\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\n**Evidence:**\n\n1. Hook at `hooks/post-write-check.sh` includes awk-based multiline detection for `except Exception:` followed by `pass` or `...`\n2. Live test with sample Python file containing both patterns:\n\n```\ninput: echo '{\"file_path\": \"/tmp/test_bare_except.py\"}' | bash hooks/post-write-check.sh\noutput: {\"message\": \"New code written. Verify OTLP instrumentation is present.\\n-> Check that new endpoints emit traces and structured logs.\\n[WARN] Bare 'except Exception: pass/...' detected in /tmp/test_bare_except.py\\n       Handle the error or add a # IGNORE: comment\"}\n```\n\n3. 4 dedicated tests pass in `error-handling-enforcement.test.ts` confirming:\n   - Checks for `.py` file extension\n   - Uses awk for multiline detection\n   - Emits `[WARN]` message\n   - Suggests handling error or adding IGNORE comment\n\n## Summary\n\n| AC | Verdict | Method |\n|----|---------|--------|\n| AC1 | PASS | Source inspection + test execution |\n| AC2 | PASS | Live hook execution + test execution |\n\n**All ACs verified. Story ready to mark done.**\n\n<!-- verification-summary: passed=2, failed=0, escalated=0, pending=0 -->\n","numLines":60,"startLine":1,"totalLines":60}}}
